{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959634,"pPcc":"SAT#P","questionId":"3de7a7d7","skill_cd":"P.B.","score_band_range_cd":2,"skill_desc":"Nonlinear equations in one variable and systems of equations in two variables ","createDate":1691007959634,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Advanced Math","ibn":"08137-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"P","uId":"3bbc7575-e2d2-4579-b41a-0c420a9db765","difficulty":"E"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"08137-DC","section":"Math","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">Which of the following is a solution to the equation <span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x squared, minus 4, equals x squared\"></span></span> ?</p>\n","answer":{"style":"Multiple Choice","choices":{"a":{"body":"<p>1</p>\n"},"b":{"body":"<p>2</p>\n"},"c":{"body":"<p>3</p>\n"},"d":{"body":"<p>4</p>\n"}},"correct_choice":"b","rationale":"<p>Choice B is correct. Subtracting <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> from both sides of the given equation yields <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> &ndash; 4 = 0. Adding 4 to both sides of the equation gives <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> = 4. Taking the square root of both sides of the equation gives <span class=\"italic\">x</span> = 2 or <span class=\"italic\">x</span> = &ndash;2. Therefore, <span class=\"italic\">x</span> = 2 is one solution to the original equation.<p class=\"tcp-9d8041ce-388a-4d17-b627-3a24b2379e05\">Alternative approach: Subtracting <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> from both sides of the given equation yields <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> &ndash; 4 = 0. Factoring this equation gives <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> &ndash; 4 = (<span class=\"italic\">x</span> + 2)(<span class=\"italic\">x</span><!--StartFragment--> &ndash; <!--EndFragment-->2) = 0, such that <span class=\"italic\">x</span> = 2 or <span class=\"italic\">x</span> = <!--StartFragment-->&ndash;<!--EndFragment-->2. Therefore, <span class=\"italic\">x</span> = 2 is one solution to the original equation.</p><p>Choices A, C, and D are incorrect and may be the result of computation errors.</p></p>\n"}}}